| c. 48 or 55 CE.{{sfn|Powell|2018|p=327}} One of the indisputably genuine Pauline letters.  The dating of this letter depends on whether it was written to the northern or southern portion of Galatia (with the former representing the later date). {{sfn|Powell|2018|p=326-327}}
| {{Papyrus link|46}} (late 2nd century or 3rd century CE)
