{{Orphan|date=October 2011}} {{Infobox software | name = ELMAH | title = ELMAH | logo = <!-- Image name is enough --> | logo caption = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | author = | developer = Atif Aziz | released = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | discontinued = | latest release version = 1.2.2 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2012|04|13}} | latest preview version = | latest preview date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | programming language = [[C Sharp (programming language)|C#]] | operating system = | platform = .NET | size = | genre = Error logging | license = [[Apache License]] 2.0 | website = {{URL|code.google.com/p/elmah/}} }} {{Portal|Free software}} '''ELMAH''' (Error Logging Modules and Handlers) is an [[open-source software|open-source]]<ref name="license">[https://code.google.com/p/elmah/wiki/License ELMAH License]</ref> debugging tool for [[ASP.NET]] web services.<ref name="home">[https://code.google.com/p/elmah Official website]</ref> When added to a running [[web application]] on a machine, exceptions that are thrown trigger event handlers in the ELMAH tool. These event handlers can include logging to various database back-ends, logging which can be viewed from a web portal, and the sending of notification emails, tweets and RSS articles to advise administrators of the problem. ELMAH provides a pluggable implementation of error logging.<ref name="msdn">[http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa479332.aspx MSDN: Using HTTP Modules and Handlers to Create Pluggable ASP.NET Components]</ref>
